Protesters have blocked the Umaru Yar’Adua Way leading to the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja.  The youths, under the aegis of #RevolutionNow, blocked the road on Monday morning. The protesters made bonfires on the ever-busy road leaving motorists stranded. Most hits are workers who live in Lugbe, Kuje, and other areas along the Airport road making their way to the city centre to resume work after the weekend. Details later….  Source #ENDSARS protesters have blocked the Abuja-Keffi road in continuation of the agitations against alleged harassment and molestations by operatives of the disbanded Special Anti-Robbery Squad(SARS). The development is making it difficult for commuters and motorists to go about their normal businesses.   On Friday, they converged on the City Gate… In "News" Soldiers and policemen were in the early hours of Tuesday deployed in some communities near the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja apparently to forestall further breakdown of law and order as the protests against the scrapped Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Nigeria Police Force continues.   They were seen… In "News" #ENDSARS protesters on Abuja shut down the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport road and the City Gate. They massed at the City Gate, causing a serious traffic gridlock on the busy highway despite the ban on protests and rallies by the Federal Capital Authorities.   The demonstrators also sang the national… In "News"